text:
The team has been making steady, behind-the-scenes improvements to Hubs and the protocol.

Not out of the woods yet, but the team has scaled Hubs significantly.

And we have a public dashboard related to Warpcast's sync to Hub performance here:

status.warpcast.com

cast.text: Since this day, we're at 50x the message count, 180x the peer count, ~40x the db size. Perf metrics are harder to compare since it was during an incident but currently p95 merge latency is ~30ms and p95 gossip delay is <1s (vs 2000ms and ~2.5hrs during the incident)

show_title: Gm Farcaster Ep139 Wednesday August 7, 2024 with guest cohost  @toadyhawk
text:
Feed freshness continues to improve!

The average cast is now ~ 8hr old, down from ~18hr a few weeks ago.

cast.text:
Warpcast's feed are becoming more realtime. 

Average cast age went down from ~18h to ~12h for the first feed load. Subsequent feed loads usually have much newer casts, since the first load is trying to find the best content since you were last online. 

h/t to @cmlad.eth and @akshaan for these improvements.

show_title: Gm Farcaster Ep139 Wednesday August 7, 2024 with guest cohost  @toadyhawk
text:
view.art is a tool that allows anyone to curate a URL that displays onchain art. 

There are three types of users who I believe will find this tool valuable:
- Artists who are looking for a simple & memorable portfolio URL that displays well on any devices
- Events teams & galleries who need an easy way to conduct exhibitons
- Online tastemakers who want to curate channels for other people to look at, like one of those lo-fi YouTube channels

It's not clear to me yet which one will be the biggest, or if there are other use cases we haven't considered yet. 

That's why I'm excited to launch: to find out who is needs this product & how we can make it better for them.

cast.text:
We‚Äôre one week away from the first view.art launch event in Tokyo on August 11th.

The product has come a long way since our initial prototype, but there is still much work to do. 

I commit to posting daily about the process of preparing a product for launch.

Especially if it‚Äôs uncomfortable :)
